RACE.RACE_TEXT: United Nations S. - Grade1 MONMOUTH PARK RACE 11 1 3/8M Turf CR: 112. Stakes Purse 612000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $500 each, which should accompany the nomination, $3,000 to pass the entry box and $3,000 to start. The owner of the winner to receive $360,000, $120,000 to second, $60,000 to third, $30,000 to fourth, $18,000 to fifth and $6,000 to sixth through last. Three-Year-Olds: 121 lbs.; Older: 124 lbs. Non-winners of a graded stakes in 2023 allowed 2 lbs.; Non-winners of a sweepstakes in 2023, 4 lbs.; $50,000 once in 2023, 6 lbs. (Should this race be taken off the turf it will be run at One Mile and One Quarter on the main track). The winning owner to receive a trophy. Closed Sunday, July 9, 2023 with 24 nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THERAPIST steadied between rivals on the first turn, settled two wide off the pace, moved up three wide on the far turn, came four wide into the lane, rallied outside, closed willingly in the final furlong, put a head in front past the sixteenth marker and drew clear under urging. CATNIP settled comfortably off the pacesetter, commenced his bid entering the far turn, bid two wide between rivals, dueled, took over turning for home, edged away to a short lead, dug in gamely in the final furlong and settled for place honors. RED KNIGHT raced two wide off the pace, moved up four wide on the far turn, came four wide into the lane, rallied outside and finished well to get up for third. LIMITED LIABILITY bobbled and was bumped at the break, raced off the pace with an inside trip, chased inside on the far turn, rallied in the two path in the lane and just missed for the show spot. PLANETARIO (BRZ) was bumped at the start, raced off the pace with an inside trip, moved up two wide on the far turn and rallied on the rail in the stretch. FOREIGN RELATIONS raced between rivals on the first turn, settled two wide off the pace, bid three wide on the far turn, dueled and was outkicked in the stretch. SO HIGH (GB) set the pace on the inside, opened up a comfortable lead, dueled inside rivals on the far turn and weakened in the stretch. YAMATO raced off the pace inside, steadied at the quarter pole and failed to threaten. KYGO (GER) raced three wide early, then pulled while two wide passing the wire the first turn, settled, chased between rivals on the far turn, checked at the quarter pole and faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TVG.com Haskell S. - Grade1 MONMOUTH PARK RACE 12 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 106. Stakes Purse 1017500. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS. By subscription of $500 each, $6,000 to pass the entry box and $6,000 to start. The winning owner to receive $600,000, $200,000 to second, $100,000 to third, $50,000 to fourth, $30,000 to fifth and $12,500 to sixth through last. Weigh t: 122 lbs. Non-winners of a Grade 1 stakes at a mile or over in 2023 allowed 3 lbs. The TVG.com Haskell Stakes has been selected as one of the Breeders' Cup Win and You're In Challenge Races. The nominated winner of the Haskell Stakes will be entitledto automatic entry into the 2023 running of the Breeders' Cup Classic Championship race and will be entitled to have pre-entry and entries fees waived for the Championship race and receive a travel award if shipping from a base located outside the State oof California. Furosemide (Lasix) is not permitted within 48 hours of post time for this race. The winning owner to receive a trophy. Closed Sunday, July 9, 2023 with 21 nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GEAUX ROCKET RIDE moved off the inside going into the clubhouse turn, stalked three wide, moved up four wide nearing the far turn, made a strong three wide bid on the turn, dueled with ARABIAN KNIGHT, then hooked up with MAGE in upper stretch, responded to that challenge passing the furlong marker, took charge and drew clear under urging. MAGE raced three wide early, settled off the pace between horses, moved up three wide on the far turn, rallied four wide into the stretch, made a strong bid outside of the winner, dueled heads apart passing the eighth pole, dug in gamely but settled for the place spot. ARABIAN KNIGHT broke sharply, stalked AWESOME STRONG early on, then moved up outside to contest the pace, took over, dueled three wide nearing the far turn, then dueled inside of GEAUX ROCKET RIDE on the far turn, weakened in the lane, then stayed on well to hold third. EXTRA ANEJO raced four wide early, settled three wide off the pace, moved up four wide on the far turn, rallied mildly and went evenly late. TAPIT TRICE raced off the pace inside, moved up two wide on the far turn, came four wide into the lane and lacked a rally. HOWGREATISNATE broke open the gate prior, raced off the pace inside, made a rail bid at the three eights marker, dueled on the turn and faded. SALUTE THE STARS pulled early on, checked entering the clubhouse turn and was rank on the turn, then stalked between rivals, bid four wide at the three eighths marker, chased between horses on the turn and faded. AWESOME STRONG vied inside for the lead, dueled between rivals nearing the far turn, then gave way.

ROYAL DAME tracked on the inside, saved ground on the far turn, rallied on the rail in the stretch run and dug in gamely for third. RUDA raced two wide off the pace, moved up three wide on the far turn, rallied three wide into the stretch, bid and was outkicked. STANDOFF vied inside for the early lead, then was taken off the pace on the first turn, tracked and failed to threaten. INSATIABLE stalked two wide, chased on the far turn and faded. BOSTON PRINCESS raced off the pace inside and did not factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEADING CONTENDER tracked on the inside, angled out midway on the far turn, rallied three wide into the stretch, dueled with PHELPSY and prevailed late. PHELPSY broke slowly, pulled early on and rushed up into contention on the inside, took over to set the pace, shook free on the far turn, dug in gamely on the rail in the final furlong and battled to the end. JUST BEAT THE ODDS stalked three wide, bid three wide on the far turn, rallied between horses into the stretch, could not go with the top pair, angled out and came on again nearing the finish. LIFE ON THE NILE set the early pace, then stalked two wide, chased on the far turn and faded. MODERN ERA was outrun early, came three wide into the lane and passed tired ones. PENZANCE raced four wide early, settled off the rail, off the pace, chased on the far turn and gave way. POWER OF NATURE raced off the pace inside and did not factor.
